---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 206
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Death=‘Die Before Ye Die'
By: Sânti-deva
---
It is well for a man to depart to the forest ere the four bearers
carry him away amidst the laments of his folk. Free from commerce and
hindrance, possessing naught but his body, he has no grief at the hour
of death, for already he has died to the world.
